Package intermediate_rep

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CypAggFuncs
    Class for mapping the different types of aggregate functions that are possible to return.
    CypCount
    Class for mapping the different types of count() that are possible to return.
    CypForEach
    Class for storing information about the FOREACH section of a Cypher query.
    CypIterate
    Class for holding intermediate information about the Cypher extension that uses the ITERATE keyword.
    CypNode
    Class for storing nodes from a Cypher query, that are present in the MATCH clause.
    CypOrder
    Class for storing the order by clause of a cypher query (if there is one).
    CypRel
    Class for storing the relationships in a Cypher query.
    CypReturn
    Class for storing the return fields of a Cypher query.
    CypWhere
    Stores information linking to an individual predicate contained within a WHERE clause.
    DecodedQuery
    This class definition bundles together all of the intermediate representations built up by the tool, as well as storing the SQL translation for completeness.
    MatchClause
    Stores all the CypNode and CypRel objects, and has an internal ID to keep track of the order.
    OrderClause
    Stores the intermediate representation of the original Cypher ORDER BY clause.
    ReturnClause
    Stores the intermediate representation of the original Cypher RETURN clause.
